From 84a03d5a6fb2c4cf6f2ce7fb58078a3e8a0b29df Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: libyaul-build-scripts <noreply@example.com>
Date: Mon, 16 Feb 2026 17:10:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] sh: fix SUBC T-bit model for PR target/122948

PR target/122948 reports wrong-code for expressions like:
  (b - a - 1) <= b

The SH SUBC machine description modeled the new T bit as:
  (op1 - op2 - T) > op1
which is not equivalent to the required borrow condition. In particular,
the carry/borrow behavior for the extra T subtraction is incorrect.

Model T as unsigned:
  (op2 + T) > op1
using DI zero-extend arithmetic to avoid SI wraparound in the compare.

This targets GCC 14.3.0 SH backend and is intended to prevent the
sett/subc-only lowering shape seen in PR122948 reproducer codegen.
---
 gcc/config/sh/sh.md | 6 +++---
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/gcc/config/sh/sh.md b/gcc/config/sh/sh.md
index 1203209f89b..bc6ab65968e 100644
--- a/gcc/config/sh/sh.md
+++ b/gcc/config/sh/sh.md
@@ -1955,9 +1955,9 @@
 			    (match_operand:SI 2 "arith_reg_operand" "r"))
 		  (reg:SI T_REG)))
    (set (reg:SI T_REG)
-	(gtu:SI (minus:SI (minus:SI (match_dup 1) (match_dup 2))
-			  (reg:SI T_REG))
-		(match_dup 1)))]
+	(gtu:SI (plus:DI (zero_extend:DI (match_dup:SI 2))
+				 (zero_extend:DI (reg:SI T_REG)))
+			(zero_extend:DI (match_dup:SI 1))))]
   "TARGET_SH1"
   "subc	%2,%0"
   [(set_attr "type" "arith")])
-- 
2.50.1
